'''Breetish widrawal frae the European Union''', eften shortened tae '''Brexit''' (a [[portmanteau]] o "Breetish" or "Breetain" an "exit"),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-32810887|title=The UK's EU referendum: All you need to know|work=BBC News|accessdate=24 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.google.com/search?q=brexit+%2B%22british+and+exit%22&rlz=1C1SKPL_enUS501US501&oq=brexit+%2B%22british+and+exit%22&aqs=chrome..69i57j0l5.11241j0j7&sourceid=chrome&ie=UTF-8|title=Google search for Brexit plus "British and exit"}}</ref> is a poleetical goal that haes been pursued bi various individuals, [[advocacy group]]s, an [[Leet o poleetical pairties in the Unitit Kinrick|poleetical pairties]] syne the [[Unitit Kinrick]] (UK) jyned the precursor o the [[European Union]] (EU) in 1973.

